Section 21 of the new Bill provides that the Legislative Assembly shall have power to confer upon territorial courts jurisdiction as to matters of alimony; a question having arisen as to their power to do that, By section 22 the Lieutenant- Governor, with the consent of the Gov- ernor in Council, may close up any road that is transferred to the Territories or vary its direction. That is the law in a separate Act, but we are introducing it into the North-west Territories Act, and providing that the Lieutenant-Governor may with the consent of the Governor in Council, do in this respect what the Assembly now does.
